{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1089,"text":"We humans have always been very concerned\nabout the health of our bodies,"},{"time":5069,"text":"but we haven't always been that good\nat figuring out what's important."},{"time":9285,"text":"Take the ancient Egyptians, for example:"},{"time":11677,"text":"very concerned about the body parts\nthey thought they'd need in the afterlife,"},{"time":15624,"text":"but they left some parts out."},{"time":17714,"text":"This part, for example."},{"time":20337,"text":"Although they very carefully \npreserved the stomach, the lungs,"},{"time":23334,"text":"the liver, and so forth,"},{"time":24499,"text":"they just mushed up the brain,\ndrained it out through the nose,"},{"time":27535,"text":"and threw it away,"},{"time":29259,"text":"which makes sense, really,"},{"time":30600,"text":"because what does a brain\ndo for us anyway?"},{"time":33439,"text":"But imagine if there were a kind\nof neglected organ in our bodies"},{"time":36637,"text":"that weighed just as much as the brain"},{"time":38773,"text":"and in some ways was just\nas important to who we are,"},{"time":41699,"text":"but we knew so little about\nand treated with such disregard."},{"time":45251,"text":"And imagine if,\nthrough new scientific advances,"},{"time":48154,"text":"we were just beginning to understand"},{"time":49895,"text":"its importance to how\nwe think of ourselves."},{"time":52797,"text":"Wouldn't you want to know more about it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55003,"text":"Well, it turns out that we do\nhave something just like that:"},{"time":58959,"text":"our gut,"},{"time":60641,"text":"or rather, its microbes."},{"time":63303,"text":"But it's not just the microbes\nin our gut that are important."},{"time":66196,"text":"Microbes all over our body"},{"time":67704,"text":"turn out to be really critical\nto a whole range of differences"},{"time":70617,"text":"that make different people who we are."},{"time":73114,"text":"So for example, have you ever noticed"},{"time":75428,"text":"how some people get bitten by mosquitos\nway more often than others?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79611,"text":"It turns out that everyone's anecdotal\nexperience out camping is actually true."},{"time":84190,"text":"For example, I seldom\nget bitten by mosquitos,"},{"time":86999,"text":"but my partner Amanda\nattracts them in droves,"},{"time":89276,"text":"and the reason why is that we have\ndifferent microbes on our skin"},{"time":92339,"text":"that produce different chemicals\nthat the mosquitos detect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96061,"text":"Now, microbes are also really important\nin the field of medicine."},{"time":99567,"text":"So, for example, what microbes\nyou have in your gut"},{"time":102032,"text":"determine whether particular painkillers\nare toxic to your liver."},{"time":106494,"text":"They also determine whether or not other\ndrugs will work for your heart condition."},{"time":110739,"text":"And, if you're a fruit fly, at least,"},{"time":113426,"text":"your microbes determine\nwho you want to have sex with."},{"time":116608,"text":"We haven't demonstrated this in humans yet"},{"time":118767,"text":"but maybe it's just a matter of time\nbefore we find out. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123063,"text":"So microbes are performing\na huge range of functions."},{"time":125686,"text":"They help us digest our food."},{"time":127452,"text":"They help educate our immune system."},{"time":129726,"text":"They help us resist disease,"},{"time":131676,"text":"and they may even\nbe affecting our behavior."},{"time":134184,"text":"So what would a map of all these\nmicrobial communities look like?"},{"time":138131,"text":"Well, it wouldn't look exactly like this,"},{"time":140407,"text":"but it's a helpful guide\nfor understanding biodiversity."},{"time":143286,"text":"Different parts of the world\nhave different landscapes of organisms"},{"time":147210,"text":"that are immediately characteristic\nof one place or another"},{"time":151781,"text":"or another."},{"time":153818,"text":"With microbiology, it's kind of the same,\nalthough I've got to be honest with you:"},{"time":157683,"text":"All the microbes essentially\nlook the same under a microscope."},{"time":160786,"text":"So instead of trying\nto identify them visually,"},{"time":163315,"text":"what we do is we look\nat their DNA sequences,"},{"time":165801,"text":"and in a project called\nthe Human Microbiome Project,"},{"time":168725,"text":"NIH funded this $173 million project"},{"time":172064,"text":"where hundreds \nof researchers came together"},{"time":174473,"text":"to map out all the A's, T's, G's, and C's,"},{"time":177252,"text":"and all of these microbes\nin the human body."},{"time":179428,"text":"So when we take them together,\nthey look like this."},{"time":182789,"text":"It's a bit more difficult\nto tell who lives where now, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186720,"text":"What my lab does is develop\ncomputational techniques that allow us"},{"time":190268,"text":"to take all these terabytes\nof sequence data"},{"time":192879,"text":"and turn them into something\nthat's a bit more useful as a map,"},{"time":195892,"text":"and so when we do that\nwith the human microbiome data"},{"time":198645,"text":"from 250 healthy volunteers,"},{"time":200740,"text":"it looks like this."},{"time":203384,"text":"Each point here represents\nall the complex microbes"},{"time":206564,"text":"in an entire microbial community."},{"time":208747,"text":"See, I told you they basically\nall look the same."},{"time":211077,"text":"So what we're looking at is each point\nrepresents one microbial community"},{"time":214966,"text":"from one body site\nof one healthy volunteer."},{"time":217226,"text":"And so you can see that there's different\nparts of the map in different colors,"},{"time":221022,"text":"almost like separate continents."},{"time":222821,"text":"And what it turns out to be"},{"time":224279,"text":"is that those, as the different\nregions of the body,"},{"time":226719,"text":"have very different microbes in them."},{"time":228797,"text":"So what we have is we have\nthe oral community up there in green."},{"time":232480,"text":"Over on the other side,\nwe have the skin community in blue,"},{"time":235294,"text":"the vaginal community in purple,"},{"time":237581,"text":"and then right down at the bottom,\nwe have the fecal community in brown."},{"time":241416,"text":"And we've just over the last few years"},{"time":243299,"text":"found out that the microbes\nin different parts of the body"},{"time":246098,"text":"are amazingly different from one another."},{"time":248296,"text":"So if I look at just one person's microbes"},{"time":251128,"text":"in the mouth and in the gut,"},{"time":253242,"text":"it turns out that the difference between\nthose two microbial communities"},{"time":256702,"text":"is enormous."},{"time":258233,"text":"It's bigger than the difference\nbetween the microbes in this reef"},{"time":261398,"text":"and the microbes in this prairie."},{"time":264131,"text":"So this is incredible\nwhen you think about it."},{"time":266662,"text":"What it means is that a few feet\nof difference in the human body"},{"time":270028,"text":"makes more of a difference\nto your microbial ecology"},{"time":272722,"text":"than hundreds of miles on Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274967,"text":"And this is not to say that two people \nlook basically the same"},{"time":277987,"text":"in the same body habitat, either."},{"time":279839,"text":"So you probably heard"},{"time":281445,"text":"that we're pretty much all the same\nin terms of our human DNA."},{"time":284453,"text":"You're 99.99 percent identical\nin terms of your human DNA"},{"time":288542,"text":"to the person sitting next to you."},{"time":290409,"text":"But that's not true of your gut microbes:"},{"time":292651,"text":"you might only share 10 percent similarity"},{"time":295138,"text":"with the person sitting next to you\nin terms of your gut microbes."},{"time":298648,"text":"So that's as different\nas the bacteria on this prairie"},{"time":301444,"text":"and the bacteria in this forest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304460,"text":"So these different microbes"},{"time":305909,"text":"have all these different kinds \nof functions that I told you about,"},{"time":309076,"text":"everything from digesting food"},{"time":310772,"text":"to involvement\nin different kinds of diseases,"},{"time":313327,"text":"metabolizing drugs, and so forth."},{"time":315193,"text":"So how do they do all this stuff?"},{"time":317299,"text":"Well, in part it's because"},{"time":319195,"text":"although there's just three pounds\nof those microbes in our gut,"},{"time":322525,"text":"they really outnumber us."},{"time":324285,"text":"And so how much do they outnumber us?"},{"time":326505,"text":"Well, it depends on what\nyou think of as our bodies."},{"time":329617,"text":"Is it our cells?"},{"time":331102,"text":"Well, each of us consists\nof about 10 trillion human cells,"},{"time":334515,"text":"but we harbor as many\nas 100 trillion microbial cells."},{"time":337746,"text":"So they outnumber us 10 to one."},{"time":340520,"text":"Now, you might think, well,\nwe're human because of our DNA,"},{"time":344431,"text":"but it turns out that each of us has\nabout 20,000 human genes,"},{"time":347752,"text":"depending on what you count exactly,"},{"time":349708,"text":"but as many as two million\nto 20 million microbial genes."},{"time":354200,"text":"So whichever way we look at it,\nwe're vastly outnumbered"},{"time":356959,"text":"by our microbial symbionts."},{"time":359791,"text":"And it turns out that in addition \nto traces of our human DNA,"},{"time":363018,"text":"we also leave traces\nof our microbial DNA"},{"time":365245,"text":"on everything we touch."},{"time":367025,"text":"We showed in a study a few years ago"},{"time":368817,"text":"that you can actually match\nthe palm of someone's hand up"},{"time":371612,"text":"to the computer mouse\nthat they use routinely"},{"time":373889,"text":"with up to 95 percent accuracy."},{"time":376186,"text":"So this came out in a scientific journal\na few years ago,"},{"time":379042,"text":"but more importantly,\nit was featured on \"CSI: Miami,\""},{"time":381595,"text":"so you really know it's true."},{"time":383382,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384977,"text":"So where do our microbes\ncome from in the first place?"},{"time":388374,"text":"Well if, as I do, you have dogs or kids,"},{"time":391021,"text":"you probably have\nsome dark suspicions about that,"},{"time":393384,"text":"all of which are true, by the way."},{"time":395363,"text":"So just like we can match\nyou to your computer equipment"},{"time":398121,"text":"by the microbes you share,"},{"time":399824,"text":"we can also match you up to your dog."},{"time":402032,"text":"But it turns out that in adults,"},{"time":404139,"text":"microbial communities\nare relatively stable,"},{"time":406438,"text":"so even if you live together with someone,"},{"time":408572,"text":"you'll maintain your separate\nmicrobial identity"},{"time":410970,"text":"over a period of weeks,\nmonths, even years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413984,"text":"It turns out that our\nfirst microbial communities"},{"time":416875,"text":"depend a lot on how we're born."},{"time":419025,"text":"So babies that come out\nthe regular way,"},{"time":421206,"text":"all of their microbes are basically\nlike the vaginal community,"},{"time":424266,"text":"whereas babies that are\ndelivered by C-section,"},{"time":426631,"text":"all of their microbes instead\nlook like skin."},{"time":429537,"text":"And this might be associated\nwith some of the differences"},{"time":432574,"text":"in health associated with Cesarean birth,"},{"time":435362,"text":"such as more asthma, more allergies,\neven more obesity,"},{"time":438578,"text":"all of which have been linked\nto microbes now,"},{"time":441108,"text":"and when you think about it,\nuntil recently, every surviving mammal"},{"time":445005,"text":"had been delivered by the birth canal,"},{"time":447561,"text":"and so the lack\nof those protective microbes"},{"time":449837,"text":"that we've co-evolved with\nmight be really important"},{"time":452287,"text":"for a lot of these different conditions\nthat we now know involve the microbiome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456796,"text":"When my own daughter was born\na couple of years ago"},{"time":459533,"text":"by emergency C-section,"},{"time":461968,"text":"we took matters into our own hands"},{"time":463809,"text":"and made sure she was coated\nwith those vaginal microbes"},{"time":466489,"text":"that she would have gotten naturally."},{"time":468529,"text":"Now, it's really difficult to tell\nwhether this has had an effect"},{"time":471913,"text":"on her health specifically, right?"},{"time":473915,"text":"With a sample size of just one child,\nno matter how much we love her,"},{"time":477596,"text":"you don't really have\nenough of a sample size"},{"time":479813,"text":"to figure out what happens on average,"},{"time":481759,"text":"but at two years old,\nshe hasn't had an ear infection yet,"},{"time":484656,"text":"so we're keeping our fingers\ncrossed on that one."},{"time":486941,"text":"And what's more, we're starting\nto do clinical trials with more children"},{"time":490398,"text":"to figure out whether\nthis has a protective effect generally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495031,"text":"So how we're born has a tremendous effect\non what microbes we have initially,"},{"time":500354,"text":"but where do we go after that?"},{"time":502271,"text":"What I'm showing you\nagain here is this map"},{"time":504541,"text":"of the Human Microbiome Project Data,"},{"time":506539,"text":"so each point represents\na sample from one body site"},{"time":509302,"text":"from one of 250 healthy adults."},{"time":511842,"text":"And you've seen children\ndevelop physically."},{"time":513909,"text":"You've seen them develop mentally."},{"time":515965,"text":"Now, for the first time,\nyou're going to see"},{"time":518040,"text":"one of my colleague's children\ndevelop microbially."},{"time":521398,"text":"So what we are going to look at"},{"time":522963,"text":"is we're going to look \nat this one baby's stool,"},{"time":525650,"text":"the fecal community,\nwhich represents the gut,"},{"time":528099,"text":"sampled every week\nfor almost two and a half years."},{"time":531268,"text":"And so we're starting on day one."},{"time":532931,"text":"What's going to happen is that the infant\nis going to start off as this yellow dot,"},{"time":536849,"text":"and you can see that he's starting off\nbasically in the vaginal community,"},{"time":540329,"text":"as we would expect from his delivery mode."},{"time":542355,"text":"And what's going to happen\nover these two and a half years"},{"time":545069,"text":"is that he's going to travel \nall the way down"},{"time":547211,"text":"to resemble the adult fecal community from\nhealthy volunteers down at the bottom."},{"time":551025,"text":"So I'm just going to start this going\nand we'll see how that happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554913,"text":"What you can see, and remember\neach step in this is just one week,"},{"time":558949,"text":"what you can see is that week to week,"},{"time":560815,"text":"the change in the microbial community\nof the feces of this one child,"},{"time":565498,"text":"the differences week to week\nare much greater"},{"time":568049,"text":"than the differences between\nindividual healthy adults"},{"time":570580,"text":"in the Human Microbiome Project cohort,"},{"time":572530,"text":"which are those brown dots\ndown at the bottom."},{"time":575006,"text":"And you can see he's starting\nto approach the adult fecal community."},{"time":578203,"text":"This is up to about two years."},{"time":579718,"text":"But something amazing\nis about to happen here."},{"time":581888,"text":"So he's getting antibiotics\nfor an ear infection."},{"time":584976,"text":"What you can see is\nthis huge change in the community,"},{"time":587530,"text":"followed by a relatively rapid recovery."},{"time":589588,"text":"I'll just rewind that for you."},{"time":593340,"text":"And what we can see is that\njust over these few weeks,"},{"time":596929,"text":"we have a much more radical change,"},{"time":598862,"text":"a setback of many months \nof normal development,"},{"time":601392,"text":"followed by a relatively rapid recovery,"},{"time":603644,"text":"and by the time he reaches day 838,"},{"time":607777,"text":"which is the end of this video,"},{"time":609496,"text":"you can see that he has essentially\nreached the healthy adult stool community,"},{"time":613193,"text":"despite that antibiotic intervention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615641,"text":"So this is really interesting\nbecause it raises fundamental questions"},{"time":618969,"text":"about what happens when we intervene\nat different ages in a child's life."},{"time":623068,"text":"So does what we do early on, where\nthe microbiome is changing so rapidly,"},{"time":626679,"text":"actually matter,"},{"time":627979,"text":"or is it like throwing a stone\ninto a stormy sea,"},{"time":630462,"text":"where the ripples will just be lost?"},{"time":633044,"text":"Well, fascinatingly, it turns out\nthat if you give children antibiotics"},{"time":637335,"text":"in the first six months of life,"},{"time":638985,"text":"they're more likely\nto become obese later on"},{"time":641770,"text":"than if they don't get antibiotics then\nor only get them later,"},{"time":644897,"text":"and so what we do early on\nmay have profound impacts"},{"time":647843,"text":"on the gut microbial community\nand on later health"},{"time":651340,"text":"that we're only beginning to understand."},{"time":653666,"text":"So this is fascinating, because one day,\nin addition to the effects"},{"time":657822,"text":"that antibiotics have\non antibiotic-resistant bacteria,"},{"time":660468,"text":"which are very important,"},{"time":662164,"text":"they may also be degrading\nour gut microbial ecosystems,"},{"time":665067,"text":"and so one day we may come\nto regard antibiotics with the same horror"},{"time":668339,"text":"that we currently reserve\nfor those metal tools"},{"time":670802,"text":"that the Egyptians used to use\nto mush up the brains"},{"time":673261,"text":"before they drained them out\nfor embalming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675325,"text":"So I mentioned that microbes\nhave all these important functions,"},{"time":678346,"text":"and they've also now,\njust over the past few years,"},{"time":680995,"text":"been connected to a whole range\nof different diseases,"},{"time":683828,"text":"including inflammatory bowel disease,"},{"time":685913,"text":"heart disease, colon cancer,"},{"time":687637,"text":"and even obesity."},{"time":689467,"text":"Obesity has a really \nlarge effect, as it turns out,"},{"time":692113,"text":"and today, we can tell\nwhether you're lean or obese"},{"time":694506,"text":"with 90 percent accuracy"},{"time":696385,"text":"by looking at the microbes in your gut."},{"time":698497,"text":"Now, although that might sound impressive,"},{"time":700786,"text":"in some ways it's a little bit problematic\nas a medical test,"},{"time":704117,"text":"because you can probably tell\nwhich of these people is obese"},{"time":707114,"text":"without knowing anything\nabout their gut microbes,"},{"time":709866,"text":"but it turns out that even\nif we sequence their complete genomes"},{"time":712909,"text":"and had all their human DNA,"},{"time":714566,"text":"we could only predict which one\nwas obese with about 60 percent accuracy."},{"time":718932,"text":"So that's amazing, right?"},{"time":720306,"text":"What it means that the three pounds\nof microbes that you carry around with you"},{"time":724118,"text":"may be more important\nfor some health conditions"},{"time":726460,"text":"than every single gene in your genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731555,"text":"And then in mice, we can do a lot more."},{"time":733792,"text":"So in mice, microbes have been linked\nto all kinds of additional conditions,"},{"time":737437,"text":"including things like multiple sclerosis,"},{"time":740153,"text":"depression, autism, and again, obesity."},{"time":743891,"text":"But how can we tell whether\nthese microbial differences"},{"time":746655,"text":"that correlate with disease\nare cause or effect?"},{"time":749418,"text":"Well, one thing we can do\nis we can raise some mice"},{"time":752065,"text":"without any microbes of their own\nin a germ-free bubble."},{"time":754712,"text":"Then we can add in some microbes\nthat we think are important,"},{"time":757665,"text":"and see what happens."},{"time":759747,"text":"When we take the microbes\nfrom an obese mouse"},{"time":762026,"text":"and transplant them\ninto a genetically normal mouse"},{"time":764530,"text":"that's been raised in a bubble\nwith no microbes of its own,"},{"time":767389,"text":"it becomes fatter than if it got them \nfrom a regular mouse."},{"time":772142,"text":"Why this happens\nis absolutely amazing, though."},{"time":774461,"text":"Sometimes what's going on\nis that the microbes"},{"time":776661,"text":"are helping them digest food\nmore efficiently from the same diet,"},{"time":779719,"text":"so they're taking more energy\nfrom their food,"},{"time":781923,"text":"but other times, the microbes\nare actually affecting their behavior."},{"time":785154,"text":"What they're doing is they're eating\nmore than the normal mouse,"},{"time":788194,"text":"so they only get fat if we let them \neat as much as they want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792614,"text":"So this is really remarkable, right?"},{"time":795300,"text":"The implication is that microbes\ncan affect mammalian behavior."},{"time":801224,"text":"So you might be wondering whether we can \nalso do this sort of thing across species,"},{"time":805382,"text":"and it turns out that if you take microbes\nfrom an obese person"},{"time":808652,"text":"and transplant them into mice\nyou've raised germ-free,"},{"time":811715,"text":"those mice will also become fatter"},{"time":813805,"text":"than if they received the microbes\nfrom a lean person,"},{"time":816846,"text":"but we can design a microbial community\nthat we inoculate them with"},{"time":820191,"text":"that prevents them\nfrom gaining this weight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823545,"text":"We can also do this for malnutrition."},{"time":825600,"text":"So in a project funded\nby the Gates Foundation,"},{"time":828688,"text":"what we're looking at\nis children in Malawi"},{"time":830871,"text":"who have kwashiorkor,\na profound form of malnutrition,"},{"time":833529,"text":"and mice that get the kwashiorkor\ncommunity transplanted into them"},{"time":836652,"text":"lose 30 percent of their body mass"},{"time":839022,"text":"in just three weeks,"},{"time":840201,"text":"but we can restore their health by using \nthe same peanut butter-based supplement"},{"time":844019,"text":"that is used for \nthe children in the clinic,"},{"time":846132,"text":"and the mice that receive the community"},{"time":847988,"text":"from the healthy identical twins\nof the kwashiorkor children do fine."},{"time":852035,"text":"This is truly amazing because it suggests\nthat we can pilot therapies"},{"time":855976,"text":"by trying them out\nin a whole bunch of different mice"},{"time":858483,"text":"with individual people's gut communities"},{"time":860413,"text":"and perhaps tailor those therapies\nall the way down to the individual level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866262,"text":"So I think it's really important\nthat everyone has a chance"},{"time":869177,"text":"to participate in this discovery."},{"time":871883,"text":"So, a couple of years ago,"},{"time":873131,"text":"we started this project\ncalled American Gut,"},{"time":875202,"text":"which allows you to claim a place \nfor yourself on this microbial map."},{"time":879406,"text":"This is now the largest crowd-funded\nscience project that we know of --"},{"time":882763,"text":"over 8,000 people\nhave signed up at this point."},{"time":885651,"text":"What happens is,\nthey send in their samples,"},{"time":888229,"text":"we sequence the DNA of their microbes\nand then release the results back to them."},{"time":892014,"text":"We also release them, de-identified,\nto scientists, to educators,"},{"time":895705,"text":"to interested members\nof the general public, and so forth,"},{"time":898724,"text":"so anyone can have access to the data."},{"time":901879,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":903050,"text":"when we do tours of our lab\nat the BioFrontiers Institute,"},{"time":906332,"text":"and we explain that we use robots\nand lasers to look at poop,"},{"time":909892,"text":"it turns out that not\neveryone wants to know."},{"time":913004,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":914286,"text":"But I'm guessing that many of you do,"},{"time":916207,"text":"and so I brought some kits here\nif you're interested"},{"time":918866,"text":"in trying this out for yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923046,"text":"So why might we want to do this?"},{"time":924993,"text":"Well, it turns out that microbes\nare not just important"},{"time":927563,"text":"for finding out where we are\nin terms of our health,"},{"time":930464,"text":"but they can actually cure disease."},{"time":932872,"text":"This is one of the newest things\nwe've been able to visualize"},{"time":935797,"text":"with colleagues \nat the University of Minnesota."},{"time":938536,"text":"So here's that map\nof the human microbiome again."},{"time":941153,"text":"What we're looking at now --"},{"time":942610,"text":"I'm going to add in the community\nof some people with C. diff."},{"time":945980,"text":"So, this is a terrible form of diarrhea"},{"time":948259,"text":"where you have to go\nup to 20 times a day,"},{"time":950604,"text":"and these people have failed\nantibiotic therapy for two years"},{"time":953715,"text":"before they're eligible for this trial."},{"time":956014,"text":"So what would happen if we transplanted\nsome of the stool from a healthy donor,"},{"time":960427,"text":"that star down at the bottom,"},{"time":962284,"text":"into these patients."},{"time":963700,"text":"Would the good microbes\ndo battle with the bad microbes"},{"time":966309,"text":"and help to restore their health?"},{"time":968388,"text":"So let's watch exactly what happens there."},{"time":970704,"text":"Four of those patients\nare about to get a transplant"},{"time":973220,"text":"from that healthy donor at the bottom,"},{"time":975124,"text":"and what you can see is that immediately,"},{"time":977081,"text":"you have this radical change\nin the gut community."},{"time":979486,"text":"So one day after you do that transplant,"},{"time":981555,"text":"all those symptoms clear up,"},{"time":983204,"text":"the diarrhea vanishes,"},{"time":984759,"text":"and they're essentially healthy again,\ncoming to resemble the donor's community,"},{"time":988531,"text":"and they stay there."},{"time":990593,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":997290,"text":"So we're just at the beginning\nof this discovery."},{"time":999665,"text":"We're just finding out that microbes\nhave implications"},{"time":1002205,"text":"for all these different kinds of diseases,"},{"time":1004378,"text":"ranging from inflammatory \nbowel disease to obesity,"},{"time":1006846,"text":"and perhaps even autism and depression."},{"time":1009929,"text":"What we need to do, though,"},{"time":1011267,"text":"is we need to develop\na kind of microbial GPS,"},{"time":1013525,"text":"where we don't just know\nwhere we are currently"},{"time":1015846,"text":"but also where we want to go\nand what we need to do"},{"time":1019397,"text":"in order to get there,"},{"time":1020883,"text":"and we need to be able\nto make this simple enough"},{"time":1023228,"text":"that even a child can use it.\n(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025829,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028058,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}